This paper deals with the efficient handling of large n-gram language models, which is a problem that is relevant to several areas of computer science. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses indexing and estimation, which are topics that are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the challenge of devising algorithms that make a parsimonious use of the disk, which is a topic that is relevant to databases (cs.DB).
